		<H1>IN THE MANNER OF THE MANUFACTURE OF ACETIC ACID</H1>
		<H2><b>Acetic acid has characteristics that are:</b></H2>

   			<P>>Berat molekul                           : 60,05</P>
    		<P>>mempunyai titik didih                : 118,1 oC</p>
    		<P>>mempunyai titik beku    : 16,7 oC</P>
    		<P>>Spesific grafity              : 1,049</P>
    		<P>>berupa cairan jernih (tidak berwarna)</P>
    		<P>>berbau khas</P>
    		<P>>mudah larut dalam air, alkohol, dan eter</P>
    		<P>>larutan asam asetat dalam air merupakan sebuah asam lemah(korosif)</P>
    		<P>>asam asetat bebas-air membentuk kristal mirip es pada 16,7Â°C,sedikit di bawah suhu ruang</P>

		<H2><b>A. Raw materials in the fermentation process of making acetic acid:</b></H2>
			<p><b>1. Raw material</b></p>
			<p>Various agricultural products containing high sugar can be used as raw material for producing vinegar, for example, fruits, potatoes, grains, ingredients that contain enough sugar, or alcohol</p>
			<P><b>2. Acetic Acid Bacteria</b></p>
			<p>Groups of bacteria that oxidize ethanol to acetic acid are classified into 2 genera:</p>
			<p>1.Gluconobacter</p>
			<p>Mengoksidasi etanol menjadi asam asetat.</p>
			<p>2.Acetobacter</p>
			<p>Oxidize acetic acid further into O2 and H2O.</p>

			<p>Acetic acid bacteria have the ability to form acids from alcohols oxidation expressed into the medium. These bacteria include slow-moving gram-negative bacteria with peritric flagella, have high tolerance to acids, and low peptolytic activity. Acetic acid fermentation is carried out by acetic acid bacteria to an alcoholic-containing solution. The acetic acid bacteria belongs to the Pseudomonadaceae family which has the following characteristics:</p>
